ENUGU – Anike Nwoga, a chieftain of All Progressive Congress in Enugu State has reiterated the determination of the party to ensure that Enugu East Senatorial district produces the next governor in 2023. Nwogu who stated this while addressing a press conference in Enugu on Friday insisted that it’s the turn of Enugu East to produce the next governor come 2023 based on the existing rotational arrangement in the state. Our correspondents report that the people of Enugu Ear District have declared that it is their turn to produce the next governor of Enugu State in 2023, based on the existing rotational arrangement in the state. 2023: Endorsement Of Tunji-Ojo By Akoko Monarchs In Order -PDP… 2023: Aspirant Urges INEC To Bring Election Timetable Defaulters… He said “there has been controversy over zoning arrangement in the state and I want to inform you that APC has zoned the governorship slot to Enugu East and it means that our candidate must come from Enugu senatorial East because it’s their turn to direct the affairs of the state come 2023. “I also want to believe that other parties might have done the same. We believe in the zoning arrangement that first produced former Governor Chimaroke Nnamani from Enugu East, then Sulivan Chime from Enugu West and the current Governor Ifeanyi Ugwuanyi from Enugu North so we must go back to Enugu East and we are not joking about it because it must happen He boasted that no politician or any leader from another zone will take away the mandate from Enugu East saying “nobody will take away this mandate from the people of Enugu East, no matter how rich or influential the person is because it’s our turn to become the next governor in Enugu state. “Any politician from Enugu West or Enugu North with the aim of contesting for the governorship election in 2023 is free to do so but we must get it right as we speak with one voice that the governorship seat must go to Enugu Senatorial district On the statement by some politicians that the governorship slot can go to any zone, Nwoga said “that’s their personal opinion and not the opinion of the people of Enugu state because based on our zoning arrangement, our next governor must come from Enugu East.